  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 54.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were in terrible trouble healthwise on top of them trying to do the very best because they were absolutely not prepared for this kind of a disaster to find.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It wasn't that kind of a unit to deal with it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They [INAUDIBLE] us, meaning the DDT went through it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "To this day, if I have got to put any kind of a cream on, I shudder.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they took us into the SS compound, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] which was clean and had bathrooms and had bunks, but clean ones.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And that's where we were transported to in the very immediate future.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "All I wanted to say is, the minute I knew that my mother was dead, when I walked around the camp-- and that was after the liberation, and the SS were stripped.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they had to run with the dead bodies to put them somewhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I don't know what they did with them at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But I had to close my eyes because I was just petrified that, just by chance, in these thousands and thousands of dead people, I might recognize my mother, which was unrecognizable, [BACKROUND NOISE] I am sure, by then, she would be.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But that was my biggest fear.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Now we were transported into the, which was very close by, the SS compound.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They have brought in the correct group of people, who were sort of ready to deal with the disastrous [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] health conditions everybody was in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "My sister was taken to a truly a hospital section and was being treated.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "She had boils all over her body, and she couldn't walk.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And it was just awful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So that's the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the compound has been-- has stayed in existence for quite a while.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
